Windowed mean¶

  1. segmenting our data in a specific time window only using certain channels (this time window and certain channels should be determined based on litterature)

  2. Taking the mean of this time window across channels and samples

  3. running statistical tests in the windowed means from the 4 conditions

If the experiement had multiple participants you would also average across trials from individuals (this gives only one data point per participants). As we only have one participant we can keep one dimension of the individual data (the trials)

picking the channels¶

O1, Oz, O2 (visual cortex) and Fz (auditory cortex)

Timewindow¶

We expect to see a MMN response in the EEG data after inspection of GFP in the butterfly plot the timewindwo of 135-200ms where deemed apropiate litterature suggest a timewindow of 100-250ms
